Why?
Thats all I need to know is why?
The high, thats it, its just the high, its the escaping reality right?
WELL FUCK YOU.
I've always known drugs and drinking to be wrong, when I was younger I didnt know what they did and I didn't know why they were so wrong, but I knew that I should never attempt to try them.
Im older now I I know what they do and I know why they are wrong and I still haven't done them but a new question comes into my head as to why someone could destroy their lives? Everything, just for a cheap thrill.
My father is a drug addict, he has been one since before I was born and he continues to be one until he dies.
He has never been part of my life, he will never be part of my life, he may know me, but he doesn't know who I am on the inside and Thats what hurts.
How can someone have a child and not love them when they are part of you?
And how can you say you love someone when you choose drugs over them?
Even though I feel so much anger towards him I know he did something right, because of him I appreciate my mother so much more, she is such a big part in my life and I would never disrespect her. He also helped keep me away from drugs because I know how badly they can ruin your life and how much I could never be like him.
Some believe that when you are a teenager you should live a little and have some fun by drinking and smoking pot on occasion. Well both of these things can lead to other drugs that are harmful and can kill you.
There is a such thing called "clean fun" and you don't need to be drunk or high to have fun.
Some peoples lives are screwed up and I understand that, but isnt there a better outlet to deal with your pain rather then drinking/ doing drugs I've heard it helps to escape reality but is it really worth your life? It can make your life worse by doing them when you are living on the streets prostituting yourself so you can get your next score.
Its just not worth that.

I wish I was cliche,
I wish I could write things that express how I feel, 
I wish that I wasn't so goddamn technical,
I wish that my opinion wasn't so one sided, 
I wish I could respect other peoples opinions,
I wish that people would just fucking get me for who I am, 
I wish I was five forever,
I wish that I still got excited for the icecream truck,
I wish that I wouldn't get so offended over what others think of me,
I wish I wouldn't lie so much,
I wish that I could have a relationship with someone without feeling like I have to impress them,
I wish that someone knew me, 
I wish that I could show emotion, 
I wish that I could say whats on my mind,
I wish that I wasnt so discusted by some people and the choices they made,
I wish that no ones parents got divorced and no one got fucked over by drugs or alcohol,
I wish I was interesting, 
I wish I wasn't such a chicken, 
I wish I knew how it felt to trust someone completely,
I wish I could control my anger better,
I wish I didn't get upset over little things,
I wish that I didn't feel abandoned, 
I wish that I didn't hate people because of the way they acted towards me,
I wish that one person could make a difference, 
I wish that wishes came true.
